decoDesc.summary: According to the foliation introduced by Alessandro Bausi, f.1v contains a big cross of one-page size. It is followed by 11 illustrated pages, ff. 2r-7r. These pages include the Eusebian Apparatus (3+7 arrangement), followed by a «Fontana della vita» or «tempietto» or θόλος, the Short Cycle, set under arches made of coloured bands. The manuscript’s decorative features, Bluetenblattstil were not dated precisely, but the XIV century was proposed as a terminus non poste quem. They appear to all be by the same artist.
decoDesc.decoNote: The first miniature according to the sequence attested by Carlo Conti Rossini, Roger Schneider and Alessandro Bausi contains a big cross of one-page size, belonging to the same style as the rest.

decoNote.desc: The runs between and is placed under coloured arches, ornamented variously, that rest on curtained columns.
The run between . The artists adopts the same decorative devices used to frame the preceding letter. The Canons are placed under coloured arches, ornamented variously, that rest on curtained columns.

A representation of the follows, as is conventional, the Eusebian Apparatus. Highly stylized, it features four columns, an interlace pattern, and a low chancel. Above its cross-topped roof, there are two ostrich birds, sitting on the both sides of a tree. The caption inside the Tempietto, which normally highlights its symbolism, is vanishing but still visible. ኑባሬ፡ ሥርዐት፡ ዘኅብሩ፡ አርባዕቱ፡ ወንጌላት።

q.seg: To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.

I have assinged gwǝlt, dedicated, secluded, I, ḥaṣāni Lālibālā, my royal name [is] Gabra Masqal on the third day of the month of Mayazyain 409th year of mercy, mighty man, who, by the power of the Cross of Jesus Christ is invincible by an enemy, son of Morārā, son of Zānsəyum, son of ʾĀsdā,

I granted Maṭāʿ of ʾAham, the name of
my wife [is] Masqal Kəbrā,fearer of God, Biḥat on the river Ḫaṣaro, ʾƎnqarʿo, christian Zaredā, including their lands and ʿĀgāmā's steep and Də’du‘, where neither ‘āqābē ṣanṣan, nor kantibā should interfere, where no other tax from anyone [sould be] set apart from ʾabbot of the monastery of Maṭāʿ. And whoever would violate it or defraud it or withdraw it, whether he would reign or provoke, whether he would be appointed or would hold rulership, whether appointed or displaced, who ever will restrain this gwǝlt, and this kǝsum, may he be excommunicated in front of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit, by the mouth of our father Maṭāʿ,by the mouth of ṗāṗāsāt, by the mouth of the 318 orthodox, by the mouth of 15 prophets, by the mouth of 12 apostles, Amen. Amen.

item.note: Translation: I am skeptical for my choice, that is why here I provide other choices available: I translate here አጐለትኩ፡ አክሰምኩ፡ ወአምነይኩ as 'I have assinged gwǝlt, dedicated, secluded', while the translation found in Roger Schneider's archive offers 'I have given gult, and I have dignified and sanctified', while Derat (p.57) offers 'j'ai donné en gwǝlt, j'ai assingné et j'ai délimité'; ወሀብኩ፡ ለመጣዕ፡ ዘአሀም I translate here as 'I granted', Roger Schneider's translator - as 'I have given', Derat - as 'j'ai donné'; ምስለ፡ ምድሮሙ፡ በንጽፉ፡ ወበቀልቀላ፡ ዓጋማ I translate here as 'including their lands ʿĀgāmā's steep', Roger Schneider's translator - as 'with their fields, and at its limit and endge Āgmā', while Derat offers 'avec leur terres, à la limite et au ravin d'Agāmā; ዘኢይበውእ፡ I translate here as 'nor... should interfere', Roger Schneider's translator - as 'nor... shall enter', Derat offers 'n'entre pas'; ዘአልቦ፡ ግብረ፡ ለባዕድ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ አበ፡ ምኔት፡ ዘመጣዕ I translate here as 'where no other tax from anyone [sould be] set apart from', Roger Schneider's translator - as 'It owes no tribute to an outsider', Derat offers 'sans taxes pour l'étranger'; ለዝንቱ፡ ጕልት፡ ወለዝንቱ፡ ክሱም፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን I translate here as '... this gwǝlt, and this kǝsum, may he be excommunicated', Roger Schneider's translator - as 'this gult and dignity... may he be anathematized', while Derat offers 'ce gwǝlt et cette assignation soit excommunié'.

CCR 7 I parte = [5.0]: (II f. 7v), according to AB. In this case textual varians corresond to "B " in CCR, he comments on p.189 'B scrittura d'età incerta, forse del secolo XVIII.' I did not find any reason not date this document King's Lālibālā postmortem. On p. 190 Carlo Conti Rossini notes that 'A questo atto deve certo riferirsi il seguente, che pero nel ms. non trovarsi con esso collegato'. Derat rightly notes on p.55 that in the images done by Roger Schneider, 'les deux parties de l'acte n 7 sont inscrites en continue, au fol. 7v-8r...'. However, as Anais Wion noticed, there is a blank leaf behind the folio in Roger Schneider images, each time when the sequence of folia differs from what later Bausi would observe. This allowed us to conclude that it was Roger Schneider himself who put two folia, containing as he considered two parts of the same document, together. Taking in account this, as well as the formal completeness of the above presented document, I consider it here as full document.

item.q: In the Name of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit. I, Gabra Masqal, granted sixty fields of ʾAham to the church, so that they celebrate the commemoration of Maṭāʿ, so that he would beseech a reward for me in the Heavenly Kingdom. If there is someone who would violate it or defraud it, may he be excommunicated by the mouth of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.

La data corrisponde al 1321. Come è noto, ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon, passanti i primi tempi in cui aspramente combattè il clero, fu poi favorevolissime alla chiesa: un ms. del British Museum contiene sue donazioni alla cattedrale di Aksum, la storia delle sue guerre contro l'Adal ne celebra la pietà, e il Gadla ʾEwosṭātewos,che ne ricorda le presecuzioni de'primi anni di regno, ne piange la morte, chiamando "colonna della fede". Nella citata storia delle sue guerre, ed. Perruchon Ṣyon alle pagg. 10, 11, 16, 17, 30-31 sta cetramente a designare Aksum, che ancor oggi è comunemente così chiamata. Degna di osservazione è l'allusione alla poligamia del re, il che concorda pienamente con i dati della storia in quistione. Non potrebbe poi passarsi sollo silenzio la diversità di redazione fra gli atti di questo re e queilli di re Lālibālā'.

msItem.note: [5.2-6] = CCR 20: (II ff. 8v-10v), according to AB. I have devided this document into three parts, with of them following next. Roger Schneider noted in his notes 'The photo is of Conti Rossini's copy A. The text starts on page 6, after CR n 19, from which it is separated by a line of dots and strokes. The text continues on pages 11, 12, 13, and ends on page 14. The writing is similar to that of n 19'. The misplacement, observed by Roger Schneider, seems to be temporary, neither Conti Rossini, nor Alessandro Bausi observed anything similar. Carlo Conti Rossini commented on pp. 203 and 206 just the following: '"A" scrittura del sec. XVI. [...]. La data corrisponde al 1322. La regina qui nominata è Bǝlen Sabā:nella storia di re ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon,riferendosi fatti svoltisi alquanto piu tardi, si parla di Žān Mangaśā,che sembra fosse allora la favorita del re, verosimilmente la "moglie piu giovane" di cui altrove essa parla. Singolare è il nome della regina e da mettersi a paro con quello di Bǝlen Sagad,su di che non potrei che rinviare alle mie Note etiopiche, Roma 1894, p.14. In questo atto, i titolari delle cariche son tutti mutati. La regina stessa Bǝlen Sabā è a capo dell'ʾƎntartā,precisamente come le figlie di re Zarʾa Yāʿqob,poco piu d'un secolo piu tardi, governavano altre province. Il mā’ǝkala bāḥr è non piu il Gabru, che vi trovammo nel 1305, ma un Samāy, che potrebbesi identificare col Semeyšaḥal di cui parla la storia di re ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon a p. 103; nel governo di Dabra Māʿəṣo, Fəqura ʾEgziʾ ha lasciato il posto a Maṭre ʾEgziʾ; lo ʿaqābe saʿat di Maṭāʿ è ora Gabra Krəstos, e il śǝyyuma Zaredā è Zarʾa Dāwit, al posto di Yāʿbika ʾEgziʾ'.

msItem.note: [5.6] = CCR 21: (II ff. 10v-11r), according to AB. Carlo Conti Rossini comments on pp. 206-207 the following: 'Scrittura del secolo XVI. [...]. La data corrisponde al 1323. Alle cariche consuete, i cui titolari non sono mutati, aggiungonsi il seyuma Aṣbi, non nominato, cioe il capo della provincia a NE dell'Enderta, sui contrafforti abissini dominanti il pian del sale e la regione dei Dancali, e l'awfari Degna. Questo Degna è certamente lo stesso che nelle guerre contro l'Adal nel 1332 comandava la cavalleria di destra dell'esercito reale (v. Storia, p.19 e 57); e questo incontro dei due testi è una riprova della loro autenticita. La carica di awfari sembra aver poi raggiunto un grande lustro, come parrebbe dalle donazioni alla cattedrale di Aksum da me odite.' Roger Schneider notes 'Follows immediately the numbers 20, from which it is separated by a line of dots and strokes. The writing is similar to that of n 20, but the hand is different, a little less trained and slightly smaller. The last line is on page 15'.

Carlo Conti Rossini comments on p.202: 'Atto non datato, del tempo di re ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon, che dev'essere stato redatto fra il 1319. Infatti, il capo di Dabra Libānos è, in questo documento, ʿƎqbā ʾƎgziʾ: ora nel 1319 era ancora Asfeḥa, eletto verso la fine del secolo XIII, e nel 1322 era gia Gabra Krestos, che continuava a occupare tale carica ai tempi di re Sayfa Arʿad. ʿƎqbā ʾƎgziʾ va quindi collocato fra i due, e deve essere stato per pochissimo tempo alla direzione del convento.

item.q: በአኰቴተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወሀብኩ፡ አነ፡ አምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ለአባ፡ መጣዕ፡ ዘንተ፡ ጕልተ፡ ጽዳእ፡ አሲራ፡ ለባሲሮ፡ ገማእ፡ ዜና፡ ኩዶ፡ አድ፡ ሕልሞ፡ ኦና፡ ሳባይ፡ ስናጋ፡ ማርያሌ፡ ሠርዔ፡ ለጎ፡ ወንከብ፡ ገዳሞሙ፡ ለመነኮሳት፡ ቤተ፡ ሰማእት፡ አናንያ፡ አዛርያ፡ ወሚሳኤል፡ ከመ፡ ይትወሀሰኒ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ እመቦ፡ ዘተአገሎ፡ ወዘተኃየሎ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን።

To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.I, ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon, granted to ʾabbā Maṭāʿ this gwəlt: Ṣǝdāʾ, ʾAsirā, Labāsiro, Gamāʾ, Zenā Kudo, ʾAd Ḥǝlmo, ʾOnā Sābāy, Sənāgā, Māryāle, Sarʿe, Lago, Wankab, the monastery of the monks of the church of martyrs ʾAnānyā, ʾAzāryā and Misāʾel, so that he may beseech a reward for me in the Heavenly Kingdom. If there is anyone who perverts it or violates it, may he be excommunicated. Translation: Roger Schneider's translator ወሚሳኤል, which I simply translitirate as 'Misāʾel', emended into 'Michael', noting 'sic' in the square brakets. ከመ፡ ይትወሀሰኒ, which I translate as 'so that he may beseech a reward for me', he interprets as 'so that he may be my garantor'
item.note: [5.6] = CCR 24: (II f. 11r), according to AB. Carlo Conti Rossini comments on p. 211: 'Scrittura del secolo XVII. Atto di dubbia attendibilità, troppo scostandosi dalla forma consueta degli atti di ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon.' Roger Schneider repeats Conti Rossini, and concludes the following: 'Conti Rossini rightly doubts the authenticity of thic act, because the form of the text differs completely from the one used by ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon. He dates the writing to the XVIIth century. It is very poor and unskilled, difficult to date, but surely late.' Many of the place names of this act occur in CCR 1 too.

To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit. Restored I,ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon,this gwǝlt of Samāz, Gwunāgwunā, Bet Nabayt, ʾAgarḥǝse, ʾAddi Gǝdom, ʿƎṣ Māre, ʾAnbasat, ʾAgāme with theirs lands so that it may be for him an instructor in the
Heavenly Kingdom unto the ages of ages, amen. [5.6-8] = CCR 25: (II f. 11r-v), according to AB. Carlo Conti Rossini comments on pp.211-212: 'Rozza scrittura, forse del secolo XVII.Ugual osservazione che per l'atto precedente: notisi come l'Agāmē qui apparisca distretto di poca importanza.'

Land of Tedrar in Ḥamḥam Qalāy and in Nāʿle and in ʾAgaran, in Kǝʾeti Falǝg granted gwǝlt to Holy Libānos King Gabra Masqal, so that he may be a guide for him in the Heavenly Kingdom. And what was granted as gwǝlt can not be counted, for it is a lot.

item.q: በ፴ወ፭፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ወበመዋዕሊሁ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡ ዘርአ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ ወስመ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ቈስጠንጢኖስ፡ ወእምአመ፡ ነግሠ፡ በ፳ወ፭፡ ዓመት፡ ዘወሀበ፡ ዓምደ፡ ለቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘመጣዕ፡ ተስፈ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ስዩም፡ ግሎመከደ፡ ወልዱ፡ ለይስሞ፡ ይባርክ፡ ነፍሱ፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ወውሉዱ፡ ወይጽሐፍ፡ ስሞ፡ ውስተ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ሕይወት፡ በጸሎቱ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ መጣዕ፡ ወእንትሙሂ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ዝክርዎ፡ ወኢትርስዕዎ፡ በጸሎትክሙ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን

In the 35th year of Mercy, during the days of our King Zarʾa Yāʿqob, whose royal name is Qʷasṭanṭinos,25 years after he became a king, the one who granted a pillar to the church of Maṭāʿ, Tasfā ʾIyasus, səyum of Gəlomakada, son of Yəsmo. May He bless his soul, his wife and his children. May He write his name in the Book of the Life throught the prayers of Saint Maṭāʿ. And you, the holy ones, remember him and do not forget him in your prayers, unto the ages of ages, amen.
item.note: Conti Rossini emended ተስፈ፡ ኢየሱስ as ተስፋ፡ ኢየሱስ.Conti Rossini and Roger Schneider read ግሎመከደ as ግሎመከዳ. Roger Schneider has in his transcription ይበረክ for what I read as ይባርክ and what Conti Rossini has as ይበርክ (may be his (sic) in the margin refers to it).

[5.10] = CCR 26: (II f. 12vb), according to AB. Conti Rossini comments on p.212: 'Scrittura del secolo XVII (?): colonna. [...]. La data corrisponde al 1459. Il donatore è il capo di Gelo Makada, oggi distretto fra Gunaguna e Addigrat, comprendente anche Dabra Maeso: consta infatti che già nella secondà metà del secolo XIV i capi di quel distretto cominciarono ad aver importanza e ad esercitare una certa influenza sulle regioni crcostanti. Ed è assai probabile che ne'secoli XIII, XIV ecc., non avendo l'Agame. A quanto pare, una unitànpolitica, andasse divso nei feudi di Dabra Maeso (cui poi sarebbe succeduto lo syum di Gelo Makeda), signoreggiante la parte orientale almeno fino agli alti monti ove ora è Endaga Hamus, e di altri capi (p.e. Dabra Damo, di Awgar Sanayt ecc.), che se ne sparvano le terre d'occidente.'

msItem.incipit: ዘወሀቡ፡ ቀደምት፡ ተርከ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ሊባኖስ፡ ወአነሂ፡ ተንሥአ፡ ክርስቶስ፡

msItem.note: [5.10] = CCR 29: (II f. 13ra-b), according to AB. Conti Rossini comments on p. 214: 'Grossa scrittura del secolo XVII o XVIII. In due colonne. [...]. Atto di età assolutamente dubbia, anche per lo stato del ms.: l'autore della donazione, confermando al convento il posesso d'un villaggio, doveva essere un capo, di cui cancellature non lasciano indovinare i titoli'.

msItem.incipit: ወሀብኩ፡ አነ፡ ይሥምከ፡ እግዚእ፡ ሥዩመ፡ ኀማሳን፡ ለአባ፡ መጣዕ፡ ዘአሀም፡ ፈዋሴ፡ ዱያን፡
msItem.explicit: ቃለ፡ መክብብ፡ ዘይቤ፡ ኵሉ፡ ከንቱ፡ ከንቱ፡ ውእቱ፡ ዘኢገብረ፡ ሠናየ፡ በሕይወቱ። ወበዐጋማሂ፡ አርታዕቱዕኩ፡ ጕልተ።
msItem.note: [5.12] = CCR 28: (II f. 13vb), according to AB. Conti Rossini comments on pp. 213-214: 'Scrittura del secolo XVI: colonna. [...]. Atto non compiuto. Il donatore di schiavi al convento è il capo dello Hamasen, che assime il semplice titolo di sum: nell'atto n.20, che è dell'anno 1328, il capo dello Hamasen è detto awfari, con un vicario (?) chiamato aqansan, ai tempi di re Zara Yaqob aveva invece il titolo di kantiba (J. Perruchon, Les chroniques de Zara Yaqob, p. 48). Riesce quindi impossibile precisare la data dell'atto, che in ogni caso non è posteriore al secolo XVI'. Roger Schneider noted the following 'The text is the second column of the page. The first column, which has 20 lines, has been erased and only faint traces are visible'.

msItem.incipit: ወእንዘ፡ ሀለዉ፡ ክልኤሆሙ፡ ኅቡረ፡ ላሊበላ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ መስቀል፡ ክብራ፡ በአልተ፡ ቢሐት፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖሙ፡ መድኀኒተ፡ ነፍሶሙ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡
msItem.explicit: ዘንተ፡ ዘአጽሐፈ፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ስዐተ፡ መጣዕ፡ ስመ፡ ልደቱ፡ ይርድአነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ከመ፡ ምንኵስናሁ፡ ጸጋ፡ መጣዕ፡ ለዘአጽሐፈ፡ ወለዘጸሐፈ፡ ስረዩ፡ ወባርኩነ፡ ኣሜን።
msItem.note: [5.12] = CCR 7 II parte: (II f. 14r), according to AB. This text was identified as a second part of a different documents, which comes here later. Conti Rossini comments on pp.190-191 'A questo atto deve certo riferirsi il seguente, che pero nel ms. non trovasi con esso collegato. [...]; B scrittura del sec. XVIII. [...]. In questo testo, alcuno cariche figurano occupate dagli stessi che erano mentovati nell'atto n.6; per altre i titolari sono mutati. Cosi il capo dei diaconi, il liqa kenot, il liqa masanqo "capo dei suonari" sono ancora Sawǝn, Za-ʾAmalāy, Bǝgwǝnāy. Fra i mutati, in primo luogo è da me,zionare il metropolita, che ora è Giorgis, il che conferma le notizie che già si hanno in proposito, che cioè, scqcciqto michele, gli succedette Isacco e che a questo, verso il 1225, era subentrato un Giorgio. [...]'. Roger Schneider noted the following: 'Voir ce qui est dit des deux versions, à la premierè de CR.7. La photo est celle de B. photo p.3. Pas de colonnes. Ecriture pareille à celle de la première parti. Ligne en pointillé au-dessus du texte. A gauche, la moitié inférieure du feuillet est abîmée avec des partes de mots'. On a different folio, marked as n.7, Roger Schneider has this text transcribed again, here he provides his notes in English: 'For the copy A, see the remarks to the first part. B is on the recto folloing n.7, first part. The writing is similar to that of the first part. No columns.'

msItem.incipit: ወሀብኩ፡ አነ፡ ይርድአነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ብጕናይ፡ ዘጽላላ፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዐተ፡ መጣዕ፡
msItem.explicit: ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በዝ፡ ዓለም፡ ወበዘ፡ ይመጽእ፡ ዓለም፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በአፉሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ መጣዕ፡ ወበአፈ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አሜን። ይኩን፡ ለይኩን። ። ።
msItem.note: [5.14] = CCR 8: (II f. 14v), according to AB. Conti Rossini commented on pp. 192-193: 'Scrittura forse del secolo XVII. [...]. Questo Yǝrdǝʾanna Krǝstos è lo stesso dell'atto n. 7. A quanto risulta da questo atto, egli pure sarebbe stato natvp del Beguena: manifestamente, come suol essere per le dinastie che dalla regione avita s'impongono su piu vasti territori ove il lor dominio è meno accetto, e come, del resto, fa anche l'attuale dinastia scioana, gli Zague cercavano, per lor maggiore sicurezza, di restingere nelle mani de'loro fidi compaesani tutte le principali cariche del regno. E anche assai probabile che le donazioni di Lalibala e de'suoi, pio che da sentimenti religiosi, fosser promosse da ragioni politiche e intese ad accaparrare al governo del Lasta il favore del Tigrè settentrionale. Roger Schneider noted: 'Photo p.4. Au-dessus tresse formée de deux fils en roulis'.

msItem.incipit: >ሣህል፡ ወረደ፡ ወሀብኩ፡ ለመጣዕ፡ ሰርፍ፡
msItem.note: [5.14]: (f. 14v) [non reperibile in CCR], according to AB.

item.q: አባ፡ መጣዕ፡ ዘወሀብክዎ፡ አነ፡ ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡ አእሚርየ፡ ከመ፡ የኃልፍ፡ ንብረተ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ዓለም
ʾAbbā Maṭāʿ what I, Gabra Masqal, gave, knowing that the possession of the world will pass.
item.note: [5.12] = cf. CCR 1: (II f. 14r margine superiore), according to AB.

msItem.incipit: አነ፡ ተከሥተ፡ ብ፡ ነብር፡ እደ፡ ሰዐት፡ ዘመጣዕ፡ ኩ፡ ለመጣዕ፡ ባአ፡ ፫፡ ገራህተ፡
msItem.explicit: በ፩፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን።
msItem.note: [5.14] = CCR 11: (II f. 15r), according to AB. Carlo Conti Rossini comments on p.195: Scrittura molto arcaica, non posteriore al secolo XIV o XV. Il folio e lacerato in piu punti superiormente, e nell’ultimo tratto l’inchiostro e in parte svanito, di guisa che l’atto in parte e illegibile'.
[5.16] = CCR 10: (II f. 15v), according to AB. Carlo Conti Rossini comments on p. 194 : 'Scrittura del secolo XVI: sul v del folgio su cui e steso l’atto 55. Croce ansata e fregio in margine'.

item.q: በአኰቴተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ጸሐፍነ፡ ተዝካረ፡ ዕረፍቶሙ፡ ለቅዱሳን፡ አኃዊነ። ፍጹመ፡ አምላክነ፡ አመ፡ ፳ወ፬፡ ለመስከረም፡ ወአመ፡ ፲ወ፫፡ ለጥቅምት፡ ይም እግዚእ፡ ወአመ፡ ፳ወ፪፡ ለታኅሣሥ፡ መኒት፡ ማርያም፡ ወዘይገብር፡ ተዝካሮሙ፡
item.note: [5.14]: (f. 15r) [non reperibile in CCR], accoding to AB.

msItem.incipit:
አጽሐፍኩ፡ አነ፡
ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡ ንጉሥ። በ፭፻፲ወ፪። ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡
msItem.explicit: የሀቦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ጥበበ፡ ከመ፡ ሰሎሞን፡ አሜን። የሀቦ፡ እግዚኣብ
msItem.note: [5.16-20] = CCR 22: (II ff. 16ra-17vb), according to AB.

msItem.title: a prayer about the king
msItem.incipit:
ወለንጉሥነ፡
ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡ የሀቦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ መንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ህየንተ፡ ሕዳጥ፡ ብዙኅ፡ አሜን።
msItem.explicit: ወያግርር፡ ጸሮ፡ ወጻላእቶ፡ አሜን። ወይስረይ፡ ኃጢአቶ፡ ወይደምስስ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ዕዳሁ፡ አሜን። የሀቦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ጥበበ፡ ከመ፡ ሰሎሞን፡ አሜን። የሀቦ፡ እግዚኣብ

msItem.incipit: በ፭፻፫፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ወሀበ፡ ያዕቢከ፡ እግዚእ፡ በዘ፡ ይገብሩ፡ ተዝካሮ፡ ለመጣዕ፡ እለ፡ የኀድሩ፡ ውስተ፡ መካን፡ መነኮሳት፡ ጕልት፡
msItem.explicit: ከመ፡ ወርኅ፡ ወብሩሀ፡ ከመ፡ ፀሓይ፡ ወበዕለተ፡ ሞቱ፡ ይኈልቆ፡ ምስለ፡ ጻድቃን፡ ወሰማዕት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን። ።
msItem.note: [5.20] = CCR 17: (II f. 18r), according to AB.

msItem.incipit: ወሀብነ፡ ዘንተ፡ ገራውሀ፡ በአሀም፡ አነ፡ ዕቅባ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወእግዚእ፡ ይባ፡ መሬት፡ መንደድ፡
msItem.explicit: ውጉዛነ፡ ለይኵኑ፡ በአፉሁ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ወበአፉሁ፡ ለመጣዕ፡ ወበአፈ፡ ፫፻፡ ምእት፡ ፲ወ፰፡ ርቱዓነ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ዘኢይትፈታሕ፡ በጾም፡ ወበጸሎት፡ ውጉዛነ፡ ለይኵኑ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ወአሜን።
msItem.note: [5.22] = CCR 27: (II f. 18v), according to AB.

item.q: ዘወሀብኩሰ፡ ንዋይየ፡ ከመ፡ ይትወሐሰኒ፡ መጣዕ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ወብዙትሂ፡ ወ፩፡ ላህም፡ ወሀብኩ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ መጣዕ፡ ከመ፡ ይትወሐሰኒ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ወከመ፡ ይግባሩ፡ ተዝካርየ፡ ደቂቀ፡ መካን፡ ምስለ፡ እኅትየ፡ እግዚእ፡ ባ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።
item.note: This text is not to be found in Conti Rossini's edition. This made Roger Schneider to think that this text was added after Conti Rossini did his work.

msItem.incipit: ተከሥተ፡ ብርሃን፡ ንቡረ፡ እድ፡ ዘአክሱም፡ ወንጌል፡ ወኅብረተ፡ ቃላት፡ ወአርአያ፡ ኢየሱስ፡
msItem.explicit: ወዕለተ፡ ተዝካሩ፡ አመ፡ ፲፡ ለተሕሳስ፡ ለዓለም።
msItem.note: [5.22] = CCR 12: (II f. 19r), according to AB.

msItem.incipit: ወአነሂ፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዓት፡ አስፍሐ፡ ወደቂቀ፡ መካነሂ፡ ኀቢረነ፡ ወሠሚረነ፡ ሠራዕነ፡
msItem.explicit: በንዋየ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ እምይእዜ፡ እስከ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።
msItem.note: [5.22] = CCR 13: (II f. 19r), according to AB.

msItem.incipit: ዘአግባእኩ፡ ጕልተ፡ ዘተገፍዐ፡ አነ፡ ተስፋነ፡ እግዚእ፡ ለመጣዕ፡ ዘአሀም፡
msItem.explicit: ወተርጓሚሁ፡ አነ፡ አስፍሐ፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዐት፡ ዘመጣዕ፡
msItem.note: [5.23] = CCR 15: (II ff. 19va-20va), according to AB.

item.note: [5.22]: (f. 19r) [quasi illeggibile e non reperibile in CCR], according to AB.

item.q: በአኰቴተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወሀብኩ፡ አነ፡ ማርያም፡ ኀይላ፡ ለመጣዕ፡ ገራህት፡ ወይትወሐሰኒ፡ መጣዕ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። ወከመ፡ ይትወሐሶ፡ ለአቡየ፡ ዘውሕሱ። ወከመ፡ ተዝካርነ፡ መጣዕ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።
item.note: [5.24] = CCR 32: (II f. 20va-b), according to AB.

item.q: በአኰቴተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ። ወሀብኩ፡ አነ፡ ዝዋቦ፡ እግዚእ፡ ለመጣዕ፡ ድሙር፡ ገራህት፡ እንተ፡ ስማ፡ ገራህተ፡ ገነት፡ ተሣይጥ፡ በንዋይየ፡ ከመ፡ ይትወሐሰኒ፡ መጣዕ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ወከመ፡ ይግበር፡ ተዝካርየ፡ መጣዕ።
item.note: [5.24] = CCR 16: (II f. 20vb), according to AB.

item.q: ጕናጕናሰ፡ ናሰ፡ ቊኖሚት፡ ደብሩ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ መጣዕ፡ ወመካነ፡ ደቂቁ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡ ወሰና፡ ወአማኅፀነ፡ ከመ፡ ኢይባዕ፡ ኀቤሃ፡ ሕዝባዊ፡ ኢመኰንን፡ ወኢሥዩም፡ ዘእንበለ፡ መምኅረ፡ ደብር፡ ምስለ፡ ደቂቁ፡
item.note: [5.24] = CCR 5: (II f. 20vb), according to AB.

msItem.incipit: አጽሐፍኩ፡ አነ፡ ገብረ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዓት፡ ዘቤተ፡ መጣዕ፡ በ፭፻፲ወ፫፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ በመዋዕለ፡ ዓምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ንጉሥ፡
msItem.explicit: ወለክሙኒ፡ ይዕቀብክሙ፡ እግዚኣብሔር፡ ለዓለም፡ አሜን።
msItem.note: [5.24] = CCR 23: (II ff. 21ra-va), according to AB.

msItem.incipit: አውሎግሶን፡ ጽደዙ፡ ዘአዘዙ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ርቱዐ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ሰይፈ፡ አርዐደ፡ ወስመ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ቈስጠንጢኖስ፡
msItem.explicit: ይዕቀብ፡ መንግሥተ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡ ቆስጣንጢኖስ፡ ለዘጸውዐነ፡ እምኃጢአት፡ ከመ፡ ንትገሐስ።
msItem.note: [5.25-6.0] = CCR 33: (II ff. 21va-22rb), according to AB.

item.q: ወዘአጽሐፍነ፡ ንዋየ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘመጣዕ፡ ኀበ፡ ፲ወ፬፡ በደለ፡ ፫፻ወ፭፡ ወርቅ፡ ወአልባስ፡ ፶፡ ወቀሚስ፡ ፯፡ ወ፯፡ ዘወርቅ፡ ወካልእ፡ መስቀል፡ ፯ወ፪፡ ፀሕል፡ ዘወርቅ፡ ወ፩ጽዋዕ፡ ዘወርቅ፡ ወ፬፡ ጽዋዕ፡ ዘብሩር፡ ወ፬፡ ዕርፈ፡ መስቀል፡ ዘብሩር፡ ፯፡ ዘብርት፡ ፬፡ ድዕም፡ ፫፡ በሬይት፡ ፫ኵኵስት፡ ፯፡ ፍሬ፡ መዕተብ፡ መጻሐፍተ፡ ፻ወመነሳንስት፡ ፻፡ ወኮነ፡ ኵሉ፡ ድሙር፡ ንዋየ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ፭፻፲፭፡
item.note: [6.1]: (II f. 22va) [lista dei beni della Chiesa di Maṭā‘, non reperibile in CCR], according to AB.

msItem.incipit: አጕለትኩ፡ አክሰምኩ፡ ወአምነይኩ፡ አነ፡ ሐፃኒ፡ ላሊበላ፡ ወስመ፡ መንግሥትየ፡ ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡ በ፲፻፹፱፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡
msItem.note: [6.1] = CCR 6 I parte: (II f. 23ra-b), according to AB.

item.q: በአኰቴተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አግባእኩ፡ ገራህቲ፡ በቢሓት፡ ለቅዱስ፡ መጣዕ፡ አነ፡ ሰንበት፡ መሓረ፡ ዘነበሩ፡ እንዘ፡ ይበልዑ፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዐታት፡ ቀደምት፡ ወአነሂ፡ ዘነበርኩ፡ እንዘ፡ እበልዕ፡ ከማሆሙ፡ ሶበ፡ ነገሩኒ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ በእንተ፡ ጽድቅ፡ ወሃይማኖት፡ ወዘከመ፡ ይኅልፍ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ዓለም፡ ፍጡነ፡ ወዘከመሂ፡ ይማስኑ፡ እለ፡ ይቀስጡ፡ ንዋያ፡ ለቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ወዘሰ፡ ተኀየለ፡ ንዋየ፡ ሰብእ፡ ዐቢየ፡ ኵነኔ፡ ይትኴነን፡ ወእለሰ፡ ተኀየሉ፡ ንዋየ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ሚመጠን፡ ኵነኔሆሙ፡ ምክዕቢተ፡ ፈድፋደ፡ ይትኴነኑ፡ ወሶበ፡ ሰማዕኩ፡ ዘንተ፡ ነገረ፡ ደንገፅኩ፡ ወፈራህኩ፡ ወአነሂ፡ አግባእኩ፡ ለቤተ፡ መጣዕ፡ ዘአሀም፡ እመቦ፡ ዘተአገሎ፡ ወዘተኀየሎ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኵን፡ በአፈ፡ ፲ወ፪፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ወበአፈ፡ ፲ወ፭፡ ነቢያት፡ ወበአፈ፡ ፫፻፲፰፡ ርቱዓነ፡ ሃይኖት፡ ወበአፉሁ፡ ለብፁዕ፡ መጣ ዕ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ወዓዲ፡ ይምሐሮ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ለሰንበት፡ መሓረ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ወይረሲ፡ ማኅደሮ፡ ምስለ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ሰማዕት፡ ወይስረይ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ኀጢአቶ፡ ወይደምስስ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ዕዳሁ፡ ወይዕቀብ፡ ነፍሶ፡ ወሥጋሁ፡ ብእሲቶ፡ ወውሉዶ፡ ወደቂቀ፡ ደቂቁ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን። ወዘአግባእኩሂ፡ ገራህተ፡ መንገደ፡ እንቀርዖ፡ የማኖ፡ ወጸጋሞ፡ እንዘ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ውድም፡ አርዐደ፡ ወእንዘ፡ ሥዩመ፡ እንትርታ፡ ተስፋነ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወእንዘ፡ ማእከለ፡ ባሕር፡ ማሕፀንት፡ ወእንዘ፡ ሥዩመ፡ ደብረ፡ ማዕጾ፡ ዝዋበ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወእንዘ፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዐት፡ ወልድየ፡ አስፍሓ፡ ወከመዝ፡ አግባእኩ፡ ከመ፡ ይምሐረነ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን።

item.q: ወዓዲ፡ ይምሐሮ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ለሰንበት፡ መሓረ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ወይረሲ፡ ማኅደሮ፡ ምስለ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ሰማዕት፡ ወይስረይ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ኀጢአቶ፡ ወይደምስስ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ዕዳሁ፡ ወይዕቀብ፡ ነፍሶ፡ ወሥጋሁ፡ ብእሲቶ፡ ወውሉዶ፡ ወደቂቀ፡ ደቂቁ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን። ወዘአግባእኩሂ፡ ገራህተ፡ መንገደ፡ እንቀርዖ፡ የማኖ፡ ወጸጋሞ፡ እንዘ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ውድም፡ አርዐደ፡ ወእንዘ፡ ሥዩመ፡ እንትርታ፡ ተስፋነ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወእንዘ፡ ማእከለ፡ ባሕር፡ ማሕፀንት፡ ወእንዘ፡ ሥዩመ፡ ደብረ፡ ማዕጾ፡ ዝዋበ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወእንዘ፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዐት፡ ወልድየ፡ አስፍሓ፡ ወከመዝ፡ አግባእኩ፡ ከመ፡ ይምሐረነ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን።
item.note: The text corresponds to CCR 14. This document was photographed only by Roger Schneider.

item.q: በአኰቴተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወሀብኩ፡ በእንተ፡ ፍቅረ፡ መጣ፡ ሊባኖስ፡ ዘነበረ፡ በእደ፡ ወይዘሮ፡ ቅድስት፡ ክሶስ፡ ወበእደ፡ ወዝሮ፡ እሌኒ፡ አድ፡ ቡራሃ፣ወነዊኅ፡ ምቅዳህሃ፤አድ፡ ቢላሃ፤ወአድ፡ መረታሃ፡ እሎንተ፡ ምድረ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩን፡ ለቍርባን፤አንትሙሂ፡ ደቂቀ፡ ሊባኖስ፡ አዕሩግ፡ ወሕፃናት፡ ጸልዩ፡ ሊተ፡ ኀበ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘንተሰ፡ ምድረ፡ እመሂ፡ ስዩም፡ ወእመሂ፡ ስዑር፡ ዘዓገለ፡ ወዘተኃየለ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን።
item.note: The text corresponds to CCR 31. This document was photographed only by Roger Schneider.

item.q: በአኰቴተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ። ወሀብኩ፡ አነ፡ ምስሌነ፡ እግዚእ፡ ስመ፡ ልደትየ፡ ወሰጓየ፡ ሐሪሳይ፡ ሥዩም፡ ደብረ፡ ማዕጾ፡ በመዋዕለ፡ ይርድአነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ብፁዕ፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ወደቂቁ፡ ወበኀያል፡ ፯፡ ሰብእ፡ በመዋዕለ፡ ድላንዳ፡ ንጉሥ፡ በወርኀ፡ መጋቢት፡ አመ፡ ፲ወ፪፡ በ፬፻፶ወ፪፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ እመቦ፡ ዘተአገሎ፡ ለመጣዕ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሰማይ፡ ወበምድር፡ በቅድመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ። ። ከመ፡ ይትወሐሰኒ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።
item.note: The text corresponds to CCR 9. This document was photographed only by Roger Schneider.

msItem.incipit: አጽሐ ፍኩ፡ አነ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ንጉሥ። በ፭፻፲ወ፪ዐመት፡
msItem.explicit:
ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በዝዓለም፡ ወበዘይመጽእ፡ ዓለም፡ ዘኢይትፈታሕ፡ በጾም፡ ወበጸ
ሎት፡ በስኢል፡ ወበስጊድ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም።
msItem.note: [4.18-22] = CCR 22: (I ff. 3ra-4vb), according to AB.

msItem.title: a prayer about the king
msItem.incipit: ወለንጉሥነ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ የሀቦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ መንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ህየንተ፡ ኅዳጥ፡ ብዙኅ፡ አሜን።
msItem.explicit: የሀቦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ሞገስ፡ ከመ፡ ዳዊት፡ ኣሜን። የሀቦ፡ እግዚብሔር፡ ትዕግሥተ፡ ከመ፡ ኢዮብ፡ ኣሜን። የሀቦ፡ እግዚኣብሔር፡ መዊአ፡ ከመ፡ ኢያሱ፡ ኣሜን።
msItem.note: [4.18-22] = CCR 22: (I ff. 3ra-4vb), according to AB.

msItem.incipit:
በ፭፻፡ ወ፯፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ወሀብኩ፡ ኣነ፡
ብሌን፡ ሰባ፡ በዐልተ፡ ቢ
ሐት፡ ብእሲቱ:ለዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ንጉሥ፡
msItem.explicit: የሀቦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ትዕግሥተ፡ ከመ፡ እዮብ፡ አሜን። የሀቦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ መዊአ፡ ከመ፡ ኢያሱ፡ አሜን።
msItem.note: [4.22-26] = CCR 20: (I ff. 4vb-6vb), according to AB.

msItem.incipit:
በ፭፻ወ፭፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡
ወሀብኩ፡ አነ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ንጉሥ፡ ለአባ፡ መጣዕ፡ ዘአሀም፡
msItem.explicit: ከመ፡ ይትወሐስኒ፡ ፍቁርየ፡ መጣዕ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።
msItem.note: [4.26-28] = CCR 19: (I ff. 6vb-7vb), according to AB, thus the same comments are applicabale to this part. I, however, decided to split what was considered one document.

msItem.title: a prayer about the king
msItem.incipit: ወለጉሥነ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ዘአዕበዮ፡ እምነገሥተ፡ ምድር፡
msItem.explicit: ምስለ፡ ዳዊት፡ ወቈስጠንጢኖስ፡ ወአኖርዮስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።
msItem.note: [4.26-28] = CCR 19: (I ff. 6vb-7vb), according to AB, thus the same comments are applicabale to this part. I, however, decided to split what was considered one document.

msItem.title: a request for a prayer about the king
msItem.incipit: ወአንትሙሂ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ እለ፡ ሀለውክሙ፡ ውስተ፡ መካነ፡ መጣዕ፡ ጸልዩ፡ ለንጉሥ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮ፡
msItem.explicit:
ወበ
ውስተ፡ ማኅበርሂ፡ ወኀበ፡ ተጋብእክሙሂ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ።
msItem.note: [4.26-28] = CCR 19: (I ff. 6vb-7vb), according to AB, thus the same comments are applicabale to this part. I, however, decided to split what was considered one document.

msItem.incipit: አጐልትኩ፡ አክሰምኩ፡ ወአመነይኩ፡ አነ፡ ሐፃኒ፡ ላሊበላ፡ ወስመ፡ መንግሥትየ፡ ገብረ፡ መስቀ ል፡ በ፬፻ወ፱። ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡
msItem.explicit: ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በቅድመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ በአፉሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ መጣዕ፡ በአፈ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ በኣፈ፡ ፫፻፲፡ ወ፰፡ ርቱዐነ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ በአፈ፡ ፲ወ፭ነቢያት፡ በአፈ፡ ፲ወ፪ሐዋርያት፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን።
msItem.note: [4.28-30] = CCR 7: (I ff. 7vb-9ra), according to AB.

msItem.incipit: ወእንዘ፡ ሀለው፡ ከል፡ ኤሆሙ፡ ኅቡረ፡ ላሊበላ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ መስቀል፡ ክብራ፡ በአልተ፡ ቢሐት፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖሙ፡ መድኃኒተ፡ ነፍሶሙ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡
msItem.explicit:
ዘንተ፡ ዘአጽሐፈ፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዐተ፡ መጣዕ፡ ስመ፡ ልደቱ፡ ይርድአነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ከመ፡ ምንኵስና
ሁ፡ ጸጋ፡ መጣዕ፡ ለዘአጽሐፈ፡ ስረዩ፡ ወባርኩነ፡ ኣሜን።
msItem.note: [4.28-30] = CCR 7: (I ff. 7vb-9ra), according to AB.

msItem.incipit: አግባእኩ፡ አነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አቡሁ፡ በአፈ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ንጉሥ፡ ተርካ፡ ዘቀዳሚ፡ ምድሮሙ፡ ለቅዱሳን፡
msItem.explicit: ወእመቦ፡ ዘደምሰሳ፡ ወዘቀደዳ፡ በጽልሑት፡ ከማሁ፡ ለይኩን፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩንመ፡ ዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።
msItem.note: [4.30] = CCR 18: (I f. 9ra-b), according to AB.

msItem.incipit: አውሎግሶን፡ ጽደዙ፡ ዘአዘዙ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ርቱዐ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ሰይፈ፡ አርዓድ፡ ወስመ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ቈስጠንጢኖስ፡
msItem.explicit:
ወእግዚአብሔር፡ ይዕቀብ፡ መንግሥቶ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡
ቆስጣንጢኖስ፡ ለዘጸውዐነ፡ እምኃጢአት፡ ከመ፡ ንትገሐስ።
msItem.note: [4.30-32] = CCR 33: (I ff. 9rb-10rb), according to AB.

msItem.incipit: ልደቶሙ፡ ለአበው፡ በልብሰተ፡ አስኬማ፡ እንጦስ፡ ነሥአ፡ እመልአከ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወወልደ፡ መቃርስሃ፡
msItem.explicit: ወያፍቅረነ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወለዶ፡ ለመሐሬ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወለዶ፡

ab.note: The edition by Carlo Conti Rossini on p.202 contains በ፭፪ወ፭ instead of በ፭፻ወ፭, which seems to be a simple type-error, for non of the witnesses contain this date and it is not marked in the apparatus. It is proved by the date, 1321, which Carlo Conti Rossini must have counted from በ፭፻ወ፭. Further, it reads ውስተ፡ ሀገሩ፡ ዘመጣዕ, while it is ውስተ፡ ሀገሩ in the manuscript, ወአልህምትሂ፡ ፲፪ instead of ወአልህምትሂ፡ ፲፻,ሰራዌልየ instead of ስራዌልየ and እሳየ instead of አሣእንየ.

ab.seg: To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.
in 505 year of mercy, I, king ʿAmda Ṣǝyon, granted ’abbā Maṭā‘ of ’Aham so that he would beseech a reward for me in the Heavenly Kingdom,

182 [pieces] of gold, two crosses of gold and one dish of gold and one chalice of gold, one dish of silver and one chalice of silver, 103 rich vestments to the church of Maṭā‘ and to the holy ones 40 fine cloths, and 30 rich vestments and 1000 cows to the other churches in his land. And after all, I gave my own golden robe and my weapon and my two pans taken from my hip, and my pair of shoes from my feet. And all this I gave, knowing that the wealth of this world will pass, so that beloved Maṭā‘ would beseech a reward for me the Heavenly Kingdom, forever and ever, Amen.
ab.note: As Roger Schneider's translator relied on the edited text, his translation reads as "In the year of Mercy 525 year'; not 'in his land' but 'inside the land of Maṭā‘'; '12 cows' instead of 1000; ሰራዌልየ remains untranslated. Then, as was mentioned, I made a choice for as 'would beseech a reward for me for me', while Roger Scheider's translator offers 'may be my garantor'.

ወለንጉሥነ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ዘአዕበዮ፡ እምነገሥተ፡ ምድር፡ ያኑኅ፡ መዋዕሊሁ፡ በዲበ፡ ምድር፡ ወይረስዮ፡ እግዚኣብሔ፡ ሥሩዐ፡ ከመ፡ ወርኅ፡ ወብሩሀ፡ ከመ፡ ፀሓይ፡ ወይዕቀብ፡ አንስትያሁ፡ ወደቂቁ፡ ወደቂቀ፡ ደቂቁ፡ ወዓዲ፡ ያድኅኖሙ፡ ለሰራዊቱ፡ እምስረተ፡ ኀጽ፡ ወውግረተ፡ እብን። ወያግርር፡
ጸሮ፡ ወጻላእቶ፡ በዕለተ፡ ሞቱሂ፡ ይኈልቆ፡ ምስለ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ወሰማዕት፡ ምስለ፡ እለ፡ አስመርዎ፡ ለእግዚኣብሔር፡ ምስለ፡ ዳዊት፡ ወቈስጠንጢኖስ፡ ወአኖርዮስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።

And for our King ʿAmda Ṣǝyon, who was made the greatest among the kings on the earth, may God extend his days on the earth and may God make him set firmly as the Moon and splendid as the Sun and may He protect his wives and his children and children of his children and may He save his army from the flying dart and from throwinging of a stone. And may He subdue his enemy and his adversaries. And on the day of his death, may He count him among the saints and martyrs and among those who pleased God, with Dawit and Qwosṭanṭinos and ʾAnoryos, for ever and ever, Amen. Translation: What I translate as 'who was made the greatest among the kings on the earch', Roger Schneider's translator offers 'whom he has elevated above the kings of the earch'; for my 'splendid as the Sun' he offers 'bright as the Sun'; for my 'may He protect his wives...' he offers 'may he keep his wives'; for my 'may He save his army from the flying dart' he offers 'may he protect his armies from the piercieng of arrows'; for my 'from throwinging of a stone' he offers 'from being crushed by stones'; for my 'those who pleased God' he offers 'among those who exalted God'.
ወአንትሙሂ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ እለ፡ ሀለውክሙ፡ ውስተ፡ መካነ፡ መጣዕ፡ ጸልዩ፡ ለ ንጉሥ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ሰርከ፡ ወነግሀ፡ ሌሊት፡ ወምዐልተ፡ ቀትረ፡ ወሰዐተ፡ በውስተ፡ ቊርባንሂ፡ ወበውስተ፡ ማኅበርሂ፡ ወኀበ፡ ተጋባእክሙሂ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ።

And you, the holy ones, those who dwells in the place of Maṭāʿ, pray for the King ʿAmda Ṣǝyon, at the evenings and at the daybreak, at time of noons, and at the hour of Qwǝrbān and during the māḫbar and by assembling, forever and ever, Amen.

ab.seg: To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.

In the 507th year of Mercy, I,Bǝlen Sabā,the lady of Biḥat,wife of ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon,the king,because of the love to Maṭāʿ, so that he would beseech a reward for me in the Heavenly Kingdom, while I shall stay naked infront of the Heavenly King, Galabāand ʾƎnqarʿo, I gave this gwəlt to blessed Maṭāʿ, my beloved, which should not penestrate neither a horse nor a lion, neither a sǝyum of Dabra Māʿəṣo nor a sǝyum of Zaredā, neither an appointed one, nor the deposed one, neither the one who reigns nor who is agitated, neither
the spokesman of nǝguś, nor children of the palace. And if there is anyone who frauds or violates this gwəlt, which I granted to ʾabbā Maṭāʿ of ʾAham, while the kingʿĀmda Ṣǝyonand while the sǝyum of ʾƎntartā Bǝlen Sabā the lady of Biḥat and while māʾǝkala baḥǝr Samāy, and while sǝyum of Dabra Māʿəṣo Maṭre ʾEgziʾ, and while sǝyum of Zaredā Zarʾa Dāwit, and while ʿaqābe saʿata Maṭāʿ Gabra Krəstos. I gave this, knowing that the whole world will pass, and I have heard the word of Ecclesiastes saying, 'Vanity, all is vanity, unless one prepares his provisions beforehead alive'. And I gave to Maṭā‘ and to the holy ones 150 cows and linen vestments and I loaded offerings that I brought from ʾAmḥarā. If there will be anyone who usurps this gwəlt which I gave for offering and for commemoration of my beloved Maṭāʿ, may he be excommunicated by the mouth of the 15 prophets and by the mouth of 12 Apostles, by the mouth of 318 righteous of faith, by the mouth of Ṗeṭros liqa ṗāṗāsāt, by the prayer of the blessed Maṭāʿ and by the mouth of the Father. And the Son and the Holy Spirit may he be excommunicated in this world
and in the world that comes. This [transgression] can not be released through fasting or prayer, begging or bows for ages of ages, Amen. I offered this gwəlt and did all this as my lord King ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon ordered me, saying, 'Go, come to Maṭāʿof ʾAham and do the will of the blessed Maṭāʿ, my beloved. And say: "Do not abandon, o Lord, my Lord ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon in the days of his youth"'. So I came and cried, wept and rolled myself on the grave of Maṭāʿ as ordered me my lord ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon. 'Do for him, o Lord, according to the desire of his heart, saying "Give ʾƎnqarʿo and Galabā, so that God give me in return for this little a lot in the Heavenly Kingdom, amen." May God give hime in return of a litle - great, amen. May God give him in return for that on the earth - that on the heaven, amen. In return for what ages - what does not age, amen. In return perished - what does not perish, amen. And may He prolong his days on the earth, amen. And may He subdue his rival
and his enemies, amen. And may he forgive his sins and obliterate the book of his debts, amen. May God give him wisdom as to Solomon, amen. May God give him benevolence as to Dāwit, amen. May God give him patience as to ʾƎyob, amen. May God give him victory as to ʾIyāsu, amen.
ab.note: Roger Schneider's translator, as he used the edited text by Conti Rossini, translated በ፭፻፡ ወ፯፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት, what I translate as 'In the 507th year of Mercy' as 'In the Year of Mercy 506.' in ስዩመ፡ ዘሬዳ the translator interprets ዘ as an element to express a genitive case relationship: thus, what I translate as 'sǝyum of Zaredā Zarʾa Dāwit' he translates as 'the governor of Redā'. ኢትንሥኦ፡ እግዚኦ፡ በመዋዕለ፡ ውርዙቱ፡ ለእግዚእየ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን, which I translate as 'Do not abandon, o Lord, my Lord ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon in the days of his youth' he translates as 'Do not abandor my lord ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon in the days of his youth'. There are other cases, which should be rather discussed for my choice is dubious: ከመ፡ ይትወኀሰኒ, which I tranlate as 'would beseech a reward for me', he translates as 'may be my guarantor'; ዘኢይበኦ, which I translate as 'should not penestrate' he translates more literally (may be correctly)'shall enter'; ኢዘነገሠ፡ ወኢዘአንገስገሰ, which I translate as 'neither the one who reigns nor who is agitated' he translates as 'neither the one who is made king nor the one who made king'; ቃል፡ ነጋሲ፡ ወኢደቀ፡ ጽርኅ, which I translate as 'neither the spokesman of nǝguś, nor children of the palace' he translates as 'neither the proxy of the king nor the pages (I am not sure about my interpretation for it makes little sense for me) of the palace'; ወለእመቦ፡ ዘተአገለ, which I traslate as 'if there is anyone who frauds' he translates as 'if there be anyone who transgresses'; ወመባእሂ፡ ጽዒንየ፡ ዘአውረድኩ፡ በአምኀራ, which I translates as ' I loaded offerings that I brought from ʾAmḥarā' he translates as 'and offerings which I brought down through Amhara on pack animals (marked with a question-mark by a translator himself)'; ዘኢይትፈታሕ, which I translate as 'This [transgression] can not be released' he translates as 'in such a way that it cannot be revoked';

div.note: ብሌን፡ ሰባ is ብሌን፡ ሳባ in Conti Rossini's edition, ዘገብረት is ዘገብረ.

div.ab:
And for this Bǝlen Sabā the lady of Biḥat, may God give her love with her husbandʿĀmda Ṣǝyon, who fullfilled his will with her authority, as a good blessed servant that pleases his lord by his service, like this she did good by her service. May God give her good reward, amen. May God give her many days in joy, which do not have sadness, with her husbandʿĀmda Ṣǝyon,amen. And on the day of their summons may God announce them the word of joy saying: 'Come to me blessed by Father, inherit the kingdom, which was prepared for you from before the world, amen.' And may He bless their children, amen and may He multiply their seed like the stars of
heaven and like the sand of the sea, amen and amen. And let all people say 'Amen and amen'.
div.note: For ወለይእቲኒ, which I translate as 'And for this', Roger Schneider's translator has 'And to her'; በከመ፡ ገብር፡ ብፁዕ፡ ኄር፡ ዘያስተፈሥሕ፡ እግዚኡ, which I translate as 'as a good blessed servant that pleases his lord' he translates as 'like a praiseworthy, diligent slave who pleases his master'; በመልእክታ I translate as 'by her service', while he offers 'through her errand'; እምቅድመ፡ ዓለም I translate as 'from before the world', he offers 'from the foundation of the world'.

div.ab: ወኵልክሙ፡ እለ፡ አንበብክሙ፡ ጸልዩ፡ ለንጉሥ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ወለንግሥት፡ ብሌን፡ ሰባ፡ ከመ፡ ይምሐሮሙ፡ እግዚኣብሔር፡ በሰማይ፡ ወበምድር፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን።
div.note: Conti Rossini reads ብሌን፡ ሰባ as ብሌን፡ ሳባ. Transcription by Roger Schneider omits በሰማይ.

div.ab: And all you who read [it], pray for our king ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon and for our quenn Bǝlen Sabā, so that God show mercy on them in heaven and on earth forever and ever, amen and amen.

በአኰቴተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አነ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ወሀብኩ፡ አንፈ፡ በዐት፡ ማርያም፡ ዘሰዐጋ፡ ሕፄን፡ ይግበሩ፡ ሎቱ፡ ተዝካሩ፡ ለመጣዕ፡ ወሊተሂ፡ ከመ፡ ትዘከረኒ፡ እግዚእትየ፡ ማርያም፡ በጸሎታ፡ በኀበ፡ ፍቁር፡ ወልዳ፡ ወዘአጐለትኩ፡ በ፭የወ፯፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ አነ፡ ዓምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ እንዘ፡ ሥይምተ፡ እንትርታ፡ ብሌን፡ ሰብአ፡ እንዘ፡ መእከለ፡ ባሕር፡ ሰማይ፡ ወእንዘ፡ አውፋሪ፡ ድግና፡ እመቦ፡ ዘተሐየለ፡ እማርያም፡ ዘሰዐጋ፡ አንፈ፡ በዓት፡ ሕፄን፡ ዘወሀብኩ፡ አነ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ እመቦ፡ ዘተሐየሎ፡ ወዘተአገሎ፡ እመሂ፡ ማእከለ፡ ባሕር፡ ወእመሂ፡ ሥዩመ፡ እንትርታ፡ ወእመሂ፡ አውፋሪ፡ ወእመሂ፡ ሥዩም፡ አጽቢ፡ እመሂ፡ ኅዱግ፡ ወቃል፡ ነጋሢ፡ ውጉዛን፡ ይኩኑ፡ አሜን፡ በአፈ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ አሜን፡ በአፈ፡ ፫፻፡ ፲ወ፰፡ ርቱዓነ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ አሜን። ወበማርያም፡ ወላዲ
ተ፡ አምላክ፡ ውጉዛነ፡ ለይኩኑ፡ አሜን።
div.note: Conti Rossini reads ሥይምተ as ሥይመተ, ዘተሐየለ as ዘተሐየሎ, ወዘተአገሎ as ወዘተአገቦ, ቃል፡ ነጋሢ as ቃለ፡ ነጋሢ. Both Conti Rossini and Roger Schneider read my መእከለ፡ ባሕር፡ ሰማይ as መእከለ፡ ባሕር፡ ስማይ. Roger Schneider did three notes not the text: 1.(ሕፄን) The two letters ፄን፡ are smaller and seem to have been written over an erasure. 2.(ለመጣዕ) መጣ has been written later over an erasure. 3.([አንፈ፡ በዓት]፡ ሕ[ፄን፡ ])The passages between brackets have been written over an erasure, by a later hand.

div.ab:
To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit. I, ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon granted ʾAnfa Baʿat [to] Māryām za-Saʿagā Ḥǝṣen so that they celebrate the commemoration of Maṭāʿ and for me, so that my Lady Mary remember me in her prayer to her beloved Son. It was in 507 year of Mercy that I granted gwǝlt, I, ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon, while sǝyǝmt of ʾƎntǝrtāBǝlen Sabā, whilemaʾǝkala bāḥrSamāy, and while ʾawfāri Dǝgnā. If there is anyone who usurps from Māryām za-Saʿagā ʾAnfa Baʿat Ḥǝṣen, which I,ʿĀmda Ṣǝyongranted, if there is anyone who violates or defraudes it, if even maʾǝkala bāḥr or sǝyum of ʾƎntǝrtā, if even ʾawfāri or sǝyum of ʾAṣbi, if even a deputy or a spokesman of nǝgus, may they be excommunicated, amen, by the mouth of Ṗeṭros liqa ṗāṗāsāt, amen; by the mouth of 318 righteous of faith, amen. And by Māryām, bearer of
Lord, may they be excommunicated, amen.
div.note: ወሀብኩ I translate as 'I granted', while Roger Schneider's translator has it as 'I have given'; ይግበሩ፡ ሎቱ፡ ተዝካሩ I translate as 'they celebrate the commemoration', while he offers 'they [the priests] may celebrate the commemoration'; እንዘ፡ መእከለ፡ ባሕር፡ ሰማይ, which I interprete as 'whilemaʾǝkala bāḥrSamāy', he misinterpreted as '[that of] Maʾǝkala Bāḥr, Semay'; ወዘተአገለ I translate as 'defraudes it', while he has 'transgresses', marking Conti Rossini's 'ወዘተአገቦ' in square brakets with a question mark; እመሂ፡ ማእከለ፡ ባሕር, which I translate as 'if even maʾǝkala bāḥr', he has misinterpreted again into 'be it the [governor of] Maʾǝkala Bāḥr'; ወቃል፡ ነጋሢ, which I translate as 'a spokesman of nǝgus', he translates as 'a king's proxy'.

div.ab: በአኰቴተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልደ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አግባእኩ፡ አነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አቡሁ፡ በአፈ፡ ዐምደ፡ ጽዮን፡ ንጉሥ፡ ተርካ፡ ዘቀዳሚ፡ ምድሮሙ፡ ለቅዱሳን፡ እለ፡ ቤተ፡ መጣዕ፡ እንዘ፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዐት፡ ዕቅባ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወእመ፡ ቦ፡ ዘተኀየሎሙ፡ ወዘተአገሎሙ፡ ለቅዱሳን፡ ይእቲ፡ ምድር፡ በጽንፋ፡ ወበቀልቀላ፡ ለተርካ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በቅድመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ በአ ፈ፡ ፫፻፡ ፲ወ፰፡ ርቱዐነ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወበአፈ፡ ፲ወ፭፡ ነቢያት፡ ወበአፈ፡ ፲ወ፪፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ወበአፈ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ዘኢይትፈታሕ፡ በጾም፡ ወበጸሎት፡ በስኢል፡ ወበሰጊድ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን። ወእመቦ፡ ዘደምሰሳ፡ ወዘቀደዳ፡ በጽልሑት፡ ከማሁ፡ ለይኩን፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። በቅድመ፡ አብ Conti Rossini has as በአፈ፡ አብ. Roger Schneider had one comment to this text: 1.ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዓት has been erased, but the letters are still faintly discernible. The copy B still has it.

To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit. I, Krǝstos ʾAbuhu,restored, by the mouth ofKing ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon, Tarkā, previously the land of the holy ones of the church of Maṭāʿ, while ʿaqābe saʿat ʿƎqbā ʾƎgziʾ. And if there is anyone who would violate or pervert from the holy ones this land, [even] on the borders or cliffs of Tarkā, may he be excommunicated in front of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit by the mouth of 318 righteous in faith and by the mouth of 15 prophets and by the mouth of 12 apostles and by the mouth of Ṗeṭros liqa ṗāṗāsāt, that will not be forgiven through fasting or prayer, through vows or bows unto the ages of ages, amen and amen. May it be so, may it be so. And if there is anyone who erase it or who scratch it in deceit, may he be likewise excommunicated unto the ages of ages, amen. Roger Schneider's translator offers 'have brough in' for አግባእኩ, which I translate as 'restored'; ወእመ፡ ቦ፡ ዘተኀየሎሙ፡ ወዘተአገሎሙ he has as 'if there is anyone who snaches or usurps', which I translate as 'would violate or pervert'; በጽንፋ፡ ወበቀልቀላ he translates as 'on the edges and slopes', while I translate as 'on the borders or cliffs'; በቅድመ፡ አብ, which I translate as 'in front of the Father', he has as 'by the mouth of the Father', which shows that he was translating from Conti Rossini's edition. ዘኢይትፈታሕ, which I translates as 'that will not be forgiven', he translates as 'which [excommunication] will not be revoked'; ወእመቦ፡ ዘደምሰሳ፡ ወዘቀደዳ፡ በጽልሑት I translate as 'if there is anyone who erase it or who scratch it in deceit', while he translates it as 'if there is anyone who with a bad intention erases or tears it'.

በአኰቴተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ: ጸሐፍነ፡ ኀቢረነ፡ ወሠሚረነ፡ ተጋቢአነ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ዐቃቤ፡ ሰዓት፡ ዘቤተ፡ መጣዕ፡ ከመ፡ ኢያውፅኡ፡ አልባሰ፡ ዘመጣዕ፡ ኢዐቢየ፡ ወኢንኡሰ፡ ወኢየሀቡ፡ ለቤተ፡
መጣዕ፡ ወለእመቦ፡ ዘወሀበ፡ ለመርዓ፡ እምነ፡ አልባስ፡ ዘአባ፡ መጣዕ፡ እመሂ፡ ፩ ወእመሂ፡ ቀይሰ፡ ገበዝ፡ ወእመሂ፡ መነኮሳት፡ እመሂ፡ ዓቢይ፡ ወእመሂ፡ ንኡስ፡ እመሂ፡ ሥዩም፡ ወእመሂ፡ ሥዑር፡ ለእመቦ፡ ዘአውፅአ፡ በቅድመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን፡ አሜን።

To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit. I, Tansʾa Krǝstos, , restored the vexed Tarka, that Tarka they previously granted to our Father Libānos, so that Maṭāʿ would beseech a reward for me the Heavenly Kingdom, so that the children of this place would celebrate my tǝzkār and would not forget me during the time of their prayers, for I have heard the word of Solomon from the Book of Ecclesiastes, [saying]: 'Vanity, all is vanity, unless one prepares his provisions beforehead alive'. May God give Tansʾa Krǝstos Heavenly Kingdom, in return for this little a lot, amen. May God give hime in return of a litle - great. May God give him in return for that on the earth - that on the heaven. And may He prolong his days on the earth. And may He subdue his rival and his enemies, amen. And may He forgive his sins and obliterate the book of his debts, amen. And if there is anyone who confiscates or violates it, may he be excommunicated, in such a way that it can not be released through fasting or prayer, by the mouth of our Father Maṭā‘, amen.

div.ab: I, Yǝsmǝka ʾƎgziʾ, sǝyum of Ḫamāsen, to ʾAbbā Maṭāʿ of ʾAham, healer of the sick ones, ኀበ፡ ተቀብረ፡ አዕጽምቲሁ፡ ፭፡ ነፍሰ፡ ሰብእ፡ ገድቦ and his wife and his children, so that he would beseech a reward for me the Heavenly Kingdom and prolong my days on the earth and protect my soul and my body, with my wifes and children and my relatives. And previously I granted, for I have heard the word of Ecclesiastes, saying: 'Vanity, all is vanity, unless one does the good alive'. And in Agama rectified the gwəlt.

div.ab: And while two were united, KingLālibālāandhis wifeMasqal Kǝbrabaʾalt of Biḥat, so that it become salvation of their souls in the Heavenly Kingdom, and for my wife may He associate her with saint women, with Sārā and Salome, with Ḥānnā and Sofiā and may He not remember her sins and may the book of her transgressions be obliterated, Amen and Amen. Let it be, let it be. And while the greats ofBǝgwǝna were qālaṗāsAbt, pāpāsʾabunaGiyorgis andʾeṗisqoṗos Ḫarayo, ʿāqābe saʿāt MaṭāʿYǝrdǝʾanna Krǝstos, liqa ziyāqonātSawǝn, qaysa gabaz ṢǝyonʾAb Yǝkun, malḥǝzoYǝtbārak, qas ḥaṣāniZa-ʾAdonāya, ṣawar nārge ma’āsareKrǝstos Bǝna, ṣaḥaf lāmSǝbḥat, ḥasgwāYǝ‘ǝqabanna, mā’ǝkala bāḥrʾAsgada, ‘aqā ṣanṣanBārā Ṣeyon, ‘aqāb dage māsarayYǝmḥaranna, liqa ’aqaytātZara Wǝdǝm, while liqa kenotZa-ʾAmalāy and while liqa ḫǝdārYāmo, liqa masanqoWalda Bǝgwǝnāy. Thus, at that time I bequeathed, without taxation or forced labour, what Lālibālā, lover of God granted. Who will restrain this gwǝlt, be that one excommunicated, amen. This was written upon the request of ʿāqābe saʿāt Maṭāʿ, [named] at birth Yǝrdǝʾanna Krǝstos and at entering monkhood as Ṣaggā Maṭāʿ. Relent that one who requested to write [this] and that one who wrote [this] and bless us, Amen.

ab.seg: To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.
I, Yǝrdǝʾanna Krǝstos, bəgwənāy of Ṣəlālā, ‘aqābe sa‘āt of Maṭā‘granted

thirty two fields in Biḥāt, so that Maṭāʿ would beseech a reward for me the Heavenly Kingdom. I granted to Maṭā‘ as an offering what Walda Ma’əkali, the owner of the land, gave me agreeing and willing, for he knew that what I took was not by force or violence. If there is anyone who defrauds or usurps Maṭā‘, whether an appointed or whether displaced one, may he be excommunicated, in this world and in the world to come, by the mouth of Maṭā‘ and by the mouth of Jesus Christ. Amen. Let it be, let it be.

In the name of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.

I, Takaśta Bərhān, nabr ʾəd and ʿaqābe saʿat of Maṭāʿ granted to Maṭāʿ offering of three fields fields in Mikāʾel and fields of ʿOnā below the land of Kəməl ʿAqabā Ḥədād in Biḥat . It will come for the monks of Maṭāʿand for ʿaqābe saʿat so that Maṭāʿ beseech a reward for me in the Heavenly Kingdom, while the monks of Maṭāʿ stay in the bridal chamber, while King Yəkwənāt and while liqa ṗāṗāsāt ʾAbbā Qerlos and while səyum of ʾƎntartā ʾƎngədā ʾƎgziʾ and while səyum of Dabra Māʿəṣo Ḫarāsāy. If someone violates it or if someone defrauds it, may he be excommunicated by the mouth of Maṭāʿ and by the mouth of all holy ones in 454th year of mercy unto the ages of ages, amen and amen.

ab.seg: To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.

gwǝlt that was granted by King
Yǝkunno ʾAmlak to Danāgǝl, to Beta Masqal and to Beta Māryām, that was violated by səyum of Dabra Māʿəṣo. As for me, I granted it so that it may become gwǝlt for me, for ʾƎngədā ʾƎgziʾ. And I have restored and donated to Beta Masqal and to Beta Māryām, and to Danāgǝl, so that God may mercy me through their prayers. I granted, in the manner [other] kings were granting, Saṭo, the land of Alāfo and Der and ʿAd Lǝgāt and Māʿṭawlo and Məkməs and the land of Mastafā together with Sarḥā and ʿAd Dāʿəro. Restored I, King Yǝkunno ʾAmlak,while māʾəkala bāḥr Yāgbā Ṣəyon, while səyum of ʾƎntartā and ʿāqābē ṣanṣan and ḫāsgwā was me, ʾƎngədā ʾƎgziʾ, son of Kwǝllu Sagada. And while nəbura ʾəd of ʾAksum and ʿāqābē saʿāt of Beta Maṭāʿ Takaśta Bərhān and while the Lady of the place Holy Mary. To the one who restored this gwǝlt, may God give him the Heavenly kingdom and may He associate him with the holy ones and martyrs and may He prolong his days on the earth and protect him himself and his wife and his children and his troups unto the ages of ages, amen and amen. Let it be, let it be. If someone violates or defrauds this gwǝlt, may he be excommunicated in front of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit on the heaven and on the earth by the mouth of 15 prophets, by th mouth of 12 apostels and by the mouth of 70 disciples, by the mouth of 318 righteous of faith of ages, amen.

ab.seg: To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.

I, King
Gabra Masqal, have ascribed, in 512 tear of mercy granted I, King
Gabra Masqal, my royal name [is] Solomon, and I dedicated this gwǝlt to ʾAbbā Maṭāʿ, i.e. Libānos,

And I granted because of the love to Maṭāʿ, so that he would beseech a reward for me in the Heavenly Kingdom and prolong my days on earth. I granted this gwǝlt: in ʾAwegar five villages at Ḥǝṣen and those [at] Biḥat and ʾƎnqarʿo, Qarn ʾOm, Mǝḥbāʾā Mandalt and Mǝgwǝlbǝtā, Galabā and Seset, in Dǝʿduʿ seven villages, in Maraganiyā seven villages, Tadirar ʿAgāmi with its lands where they are. I gave to Maṭāʿ gold and 340 rich vestments and to the holy ones 40 linen and 1000 cows and 20 manasānest and five pans taken from my hip and five pair of shoes from my feet and one cross of gold and one dish of gold and one chalice of gold one chalice of silver, one dish of silver and two dishes of dǝʿm, candles and incense without number and for other churches in his land 30 rich vestments. All this donated I, King
Gabra Masqal, knowing that the wealth of this world will pas and I have heard the word of Ecclesiastes saying, 'Vanity, all is vanity, unless one prepares his provisions beforehead alive'. And I gave to Maṭā‘ and to the holy ones, I, Krǝstos ʾAbuhu to Maṭāʿ of ʾAham as my lord ordered me, [being] sǝyum of ʾƎntartā and māʾǝkala baḥǝr Tǝwāzāt and while ḥasgwā and ʿaqānṣān Bāḥra Sagad son of the king. And under him [is] makwannǝn Krǝstos ʾAbuhu. While ḥedug of ʾƎnbā Sannāyt ʾAyso, while maʾasare nǝgus Kāḥsu Walda Nolāwi and while ʿāqābe saʿāt Maṭāʿ Gabra Krǝstos, son of Barnābās. They made this written, being together in the refuge of gathering, when God gave to
Gabra Masqal in its entirety. And into this gwǝlt that
I granted to ʾAbbā Maṭāʿ, should not interfere neither sǝyum nor displaced one, neither makwannǝn nor someone powerful, nor spokesman of nǝgus, neither a lion or a horse, nor māʾǝkala baḥǝr, neither an ʾawfāri nor a spokesman of ʾawfāri, neither sǝyum of ʾAwegar, nor administrator of ʾAwegar, neither sǝyum of Dabra Māʿəṣo, nor its ḥədug, neither sǝyum of Zaredā or an administrator of Zaredā, neither ʾawfāri of Ḥamāsen, nor ʿaqānṣān of Ḥamāsen. No one should enter Maraganyā, Dǝʿduʿ and Ḥǝṣen, gwǝlts for Maṭāʿ of ʾAham, which granted I, King
Solomon. And there is anyone who violates it or usurps it, may he excommunicated by the mouth of 15 prophets and by the mouth of 12 apostles, by the mouth of 24 priestes of heaven, by 318 righteous in faith and by the mouth of 15 prophets and by the mouth of 12 apostles and by the mouth of Ṗeṭros liqa ṗāṗāsāt, by the prayers of blessed Maṭāʿ, by the mouth of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit may he be excommunicated in this world and in the world that comes, that will not be forgiven through fasting or prayer, through vows or bows unto the ages of ages, amen.

div.ab:
And for our King
Gabra Masqal may God give him Heavenly Kingdom in return for this little a lot, amen. May God give hime in return of a litle - great. May God give him in return for that on the earth - that on the heaven, amen. May God give him in return for what ages what does not ages, amen, in return for what perishes - what does not perish, amen. And may He prolong his days on the earth, amen. div.ab: To the glory of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit. In 503 year of mercy Yāʿǝbika ʾƎgziʾ granted, so that those who stay in the monastic place may celebrate the commemoration of Maṭāʿ, a gwǝlt of what name is Qarn ʾOm, which has no tribute or obligation, which has no charge or responsibility (tasṭā), which will not expire and has no expiration, where should not enter a horse or an animal, where should not enter sǝyum of Zaredā and ʿaqābe saʿat, no one apart from the children of this place who will celebrate the commemoration of Yāʿǝbika ʾƎgziʾ. And if anyone usurps it or violates it, be it sǝyum of Zaredā or ʿaqābe saʿat, be it makwannǝn or sǝyum of Dabra Māʿəṣo, be it ḥǝdug or be it baʿaltetu, may he be excommunicated in the heaven and on the earth by the mouth of Ṗeṭros, head of the apostles, by the mouth of 318 righteous of faith, amen. And the one who made it to be written is Yāʿǝbika ʾƎgziʾ of ʾƎnbā Sannāyt, while sǝyum of ʾƎntartā Yāʿǝbika ʾƎgziʾ and Fǝqura ʾƎgziʾ seyum of Dabra Māʿəṣo, while sǝyum of Zaredā Yāʿǝbika ʾƎgziʾdāy. and while ʿaqābe saʿat of Maṭāʿ ʾAsfəḥa and the one who translated, Yǝsḥaq, nǝbura ʾǝd of ʾAksum and nǝbura ʾǝd of Dāmǝmo Yāfqǝrana ʾƎgziʾ and ʿaqābe saʿat of Dabra Zayt Tasfā Ṣəyon. and may He prolong days on the earth for makwannǝn Yāʿǝbika ʾƎgziʾ and may God make him set firmly as the Moon and splendid as the Sun and And on the day of his death, may He count him among the saints and martyrs upon the ages of ages, amen and amen.
